<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10923] Control where to put meta region</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10923</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a concern on placing meta regions on the master, as in the comments of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10569&quot; title=&quot;Co-locate meta and master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-10569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I was thinking we should have a configuration for a load balancer to decide where to put it.  Adjusting this configuration we can control whether to put the meta on master, or other region server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12706986">HBASE-10923</key>
